summary.name: Iowa Electricity Generation
summary.dataset_description: This dataset contains information about electricity generation in Iowa from different sources between 2001 and 2017.

properties.description: The year in which the electricity was generated.
The source of energy used for electricity generation.
The net amount of electricity generated in a given year, measured in thousand megawatt-hours.

goals.question: What is the trend in net electricity generation over the years?
goals.visualization: line chart of net_generation over year
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there has been an increase or decrease in electricity generation over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of net electricity generation by energy source?
goals.visualization: stacked bar chart of net_generation by source
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand which energy source is contributing the most to electricity generation in Iowa.

goals.question: What is the proportion of renewable energy sources in electricity generation over the years?
goals.visualization: area chart of net_generation by year, with renewable energy sources highlighted
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the trend in the use of renewable energy sources for electricity generation over the years.

goals.question: What is the average net electricity generation by energy source?
goals.visualization: bar chart of average net_generation by source
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand which energy source has the highest average net electricity generation.

goals.question: What is the correlation between net electricity generation and year?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of net_generation over year
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand if there is a correlation between net electricity generation and year, and if so, what kind of correlation it is.

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby('year')['net_generation'].sum().reset_index()
    
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['net_generation'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the trend in net electricity generation over the years?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    data_pivot = data.pivot(index='year', columns='source', values='net_generation')
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data_pivot.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    
    plt.title("What is the distribution of net electricity generation by energy source?")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation (thousand MWh)')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    data_renewable = data[data['source'] == 'Renewables']
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.stackplot(data_renewable['year'], data_renewable['net_generation'], labels=['Renewables'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Net Generation (thousand MWh)')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    plt.title('What is the proportion of renewable energy sources in electricity generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='ignore')
    avg_net_generation = data.groupby('source')['net_generation'].mean()
    
    ax = avg_net_generation.plot(kind='bar')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the average net electricity generation by energy source?")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
